This paper deals with the problem of sense analysis in machine translation, which is a common topic in the field of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The proposed method involves using contextual features to select the correct noun sense, which is a technique commonly used in natural language processing and machine learning (cs.AI, cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of co-occurrence relations, which is a common technique in information retrieval (cs.IR) and neural networks (cs.NE).
